Part 4: Resizing (Rehashing)

The table checks the load factor after each insertion:

loadFactor = currentSize / capacity;


If the load factor exceeds 0.75, the table doubles its capacity and all elements are reinserted into the new table.

During rehashing, the collision count is reset and recomputed for the new table.

